content.detailedDescription: I went out to walk the dog before bed at about 10pm. i noticed lights moving toward me coming from the north moving south. they were high but fairly bright. they were moving at a fairly high rate of speed and seemed to be too fast for commercial aircraft. i opens the door and called for my wife kris to come and see what i was seeing. we continued to watch as the passed over for about 20 minutes. at any one time we were watching 2 to 3 or more at times. some just continued to move from north to south and some changed directions slightly at times. all seemed to be ascending as the flew away from us. they all pulsated from white to a reddish orange color. we did not see the actual objects or craft as they were high in the sky and it was dark out. they were certainly not commercial aircraft, starts, comets or any other known objects. we were both convinced these were ufo's and a lot of them.
content.summary: Saw multiple, more than 10 pulsating lights traveling from north to south. they pulsed from white to reddish orange. some changed direction and some ascended..

content.detailedDescription:
Standing outside with my friend watching the geminid meteor shower december 13 2015 at about 10pm. my friend asked "what is that? is it moving, or am i seeing things?" and pointed above our roof, so i looked up and saw what appeared to be a teeny tiny, but extra bright, version of the big dipper constellation. i initially asked "the little dipper isn't that miniature, right?" and my friend gave me a look before confirming no, of course not. 

the tiny non-constelation was sitting in a place that i had never seen stars before, and where my friend confirmed no stars had been visible ever before. after we stared for a few minutes more lights turned on, and instead of looking like mini dipper, it then appeared to have 2 parallel slightly curved rows of about 7 lights each. the lights blinked or flickered individually, but not in any particular pattern. one light, in the middle on the upper row, that had previously appeared to be the start of the mini dippers handle, didn't seem to blink and was brighter than the others.

it had been stationary (aside form the blinking), and we couldn't tell how far up it was, just that it was above the clouds. there was no sound coming from it, but i had been on the phone with my mom for about half an hour precluding the sighting and for the duration of it (relaying what i was seeing on the phone). my phone did break up quite noticeably when we were standing beneath it. 

after we watched it for maybe 10 minutes, the lights looked bigger (as if moving towards up) and then smaller (as if moving away), though staying in the same basic position as it had been the whole time. the lights very slowly got dimmer over the course of about 10 more minutes, until they disappeared completely. 

i tried to take a photo with my cellphone, unfortunately that didn't work because cellphone cameras are kind of weak, so i drew a picture of what we saw instead.
content.summary: Miniature big-dipper-like ufo seen during geminid meteor shower

content.detailedDescription:
7:00 pm sitting on front porch facing north, no clouds and could see a few stars. a twinkling star like object caught my eye at 7:10 at about 45 degrees off horizon, nw of dallas at approximately 60k to 100k feet high. it was wobbling in place for about 5 minutes then started moving away towards n west. it would do slow loops and it dropped about 2 or 3 degrees and then rose back up. did this several times and then a blue light dropped from it towards earth and disappeared from view. the original object was still moving away from me and i saw a bright red flash about 1 degree below it that disappeared also. watched it for 45 minutes until it wobbled and twinkled out of site. two other witnesses saw the whole thing. several planes flew through my field of view during the sighting since i am 3 miles north of love field, but one large aircraft flew by silently, the others we heard loudly. it was all very strange !
keep your eyes to the skies, the truth is out there !
content.flightPath: Stationary,Hovering then path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering

content.detailedDescription: It was about 6 pm on a sunday. it was an hour past dusk. went out on the porch to have a smoke. looked straight ahead to the west and saw a crescent moon shaped smudge of light in the overcast sky. i only glanced at it at first, dismissing it as the moon. it quickly occured to me, that the moon was never visible from my vantage point. i looked more intently,and saw what looked like a blurry image of a spiral galaxy. i went back into the house and picked up my scoped rifle, turning off the lights as i went out. i turned the scope magnification to nine and looked. i could clearly see a series of stationary lights in a crescent shape. i immediately called for my wife to come and see. i pointed out the light in the sky and looked through the scope, hoping to show her, but the lights were quickly fading. they were no longer visible within seconds.
content.summary: Lights in sky

content.detailedDescription: I was driving home from working a 12 hour shift. i left work at 8:06 pm that night and it takes approximately 30 minutes for me to get home. i stopped on hwy 153 for about a minute to check for damage to my car because i had run over a piece of debris that looked like rubber from a tire off of an 18 wheeler that was in the road. i didn't see any major damage that would prevent me from driving home so i got back in my car lit a cigarette and continued on my way. as i turned onto webb rd from hwy 58 i noticed what i first thought to be an airplane. it had several lights 3 were brighter than the rest and one on the left side was much smaller and blinking. i thought to myself wow that plane is really low and it was pretty far from where i generally see them as they approach the local airport. as i kept driving towards it i realized it wasn't moving. so i thought it must be a group of 3 helicopters. i thought this for a moment because helicopters are the only things i know of that hover like this or move slow enough to appear to be hovering. also there were 3 main lights pointing straight out almost like head lights on a car. and having lived on and around a military base for about 5 year's i know they sometimes fly in a v formation of 3. however i quickly dismissed this idea because there were 3 lights on either side of the central light that were dimmer. as i drove closer i saw that the lights were not independent of each other so i thought maybe they had put up a new cell tower on hwy 58 and it just appeared to be above the apartments. but as i got even closer i slowed down because i realized it was a solid black triangle that connected the lights and it was hovering just below the tree line about 50 feet above one if the apartment buildings. i saw there was no pole or anything else keeping it up. it was just sitting there. the 3 main lights looked straight ahead like headlights on a car and you could see the mist swirling through the light. the smaller lights on either side were more like ambient light than headlights. by this i mean the type of light u would see given off from a window as you drove past a house at night. the blinking light was even smaller than the secondary lights but appeared to be the same intensity. all the light was pure white in color. the object itself was black but not black like the way we color things black, it was the definition of black. a total absence of color. it was almost like what i would imagine looking into a black hole would be like. there were lights on in the parking lot of the apartments but they were not reflected on the craft and did not light it up. it was as though it absorbed the light. at this point i was passing it with it on my passenger side.  as i continued to drive past it i saw that it was a little less than one story high triangle shaped for sure. and about one third the size of the apartment unit it was hovering over. i also didn't hear any noise coming from it. my window was down on the driver side because i smoke. it was below the treeline but again about 50 feet above the apartments. as i realized what i was looking at i said out loud what the f***. i started to stop but there was a car behind me that appeared to be going way faster than me. i was driving about 12 mph at this time and the usual speed in this road is 35 i think. i continued to try to see it but lost it as i went over the hill and the trees obstructed my view. anyway i  sped up to get home quickly to check on my children. they were home alone while i was working and i only live a few blocks from where i saw it. once i got home i gathered my children and raced back to show them. i wanted witnesses to justify that i wasn't completely crazy. but as we went back i saw it was gone. i have gone past there several times since and there is absolutely nothing in the parking lot or that can bee seen from that road that could possibly explain what i saw.
content.summary: I saw a triangle shaped ufo hovering over apartments near my home.

content.detailedDescription:
On august 1st, 2015 was vacationing in cancun mexico and visited the chichen itza mayan ruins that day with two other friends. also, august 1st, was the day of the blue-moon. i took many pictures and recordings with my cell phone that day in various areas around the ruins, as hundreds of people did. i did not see nor hear anything out of the norm that day. just took beautiful pictures of the ruins.

the following morning i woke up and  picked up up my cell phone  -samsung note 4- to review the pictures and footage from the day before, my trip to chichen itza. there was one video recording i took which really stood out. what i captured is probably some of the most clear ufo/extraterrestrial technology evidence ever recorded on film.

the recording is of me standing near the center of the ball court where mayan priest would play the ball game of death. there are two straight solid walls, one to my left and right. both walls have one ring six meters high where the ball had to go through. i hit play to start recording and spun around to take a 360 degree recording of the ball court and took 23 seconds of video/audio. between the 1 and 2 second mark i captured a boomerang shaped object fly out of the wall near the ring to my left which was no more that 25-30 yards away from me. once the object exited the wall it changes size and shape. the object then flew over our heads faster than the speed of sound as it changed shape. 

the wall -  the wall is solid but the object came out of the wall where there was a really dark stain on the wall, similar to what they call desert varnish at the grand canyon. you can see a gray "v" shaped object traveling from a distance inside the wall and get larger as it gets closer. it almost looks like the "v" shaped object is flying in space behind the wall. the small "v" shaped object then exits the wall, almost as if it crossed a portal or worm hole. as if the wall was hollow.

once it exits the wall - once the small "v"shaped object exits the wall it seem to turn towards the wall and slow down, almost like hitting it's air-breaks. at the same time it hits it's "air-breaks" the object flips and becomes much larger in size and turn from a small gray "v" to a large black boomerang shaped object. the object then flies over our head much faster than the speed of sound. i use the word "flies" loosely as it looked like it was tumbling or coming in and out of space/time/reality.All this happens in .5 seconds. when you do a frame by frame on a high end computer, there are 10 video frames of the object. in 8 of 10 frames the object changes shape. see the attached drawings of all the shapes it takes. 

the footage is high resolution and  you can see the details as clear as day, especially when you see the footage in 3d. you can see the texture of the object, even the light of the sun reflecting off the metal surface. you can also see a reddish-brown membrane type of material, as well an antennae, the antennae has a ball at the end.  i asked many locals if they have ever seen any birds, bats or insects which look or fly as fast as the object captured on film? every single one of the locals said "no" and followed up that i had captured evidence of an extraterrestrial craft. it looks almost like a drone. it breaks many laws of physics, it does not make a sound nor cast a shadow.   

the video has been copy righted and cannot be shared without my consent.
content.summary: Evidence of alien technology taken in chichen itza on 8/1/15

content.detailedDescription:
Approx sometime between 11:30 and 12:30 pm.  from wilmington north carolina i  and towards the west southwest at about 30 degrees from my position in elevation i saw 3 red   lights in a triangle formation move in a straight line across the whole skyscape going e/ne path. completely silent, very high elevation , perhaps at the altitude of a jetliner cruising at its max altitude. but the things that struck me immediately as this being a ufo are 4 key points: 
1.) 3 red lights that did not pulsate, flew in fixated position and only three red lights, no spotlights, no green , blue, yellow, or white lights blinking as you would see in all other aircraft.
2.) completely silent, no trail of any kind, 
3.) moved across the entire skyscape afrom one side to the other as far as eye could see in only approximately 5-7 seconds.
4.) viewing with powerful binoculars,    this is what i found very strand and interesting, approximately 25-35 minutes later if not sooner a , what i gathered was a military helicopter from the sound and formation of the lights was seen 1/2 mile or so up in the north sky slowly circling and intermittently hovered for a few minutes here and there with its spotlight on and facing horizontal from chopper looking straight out most of the time as if it was searching for something or possibly had made some kind of visual or contact, though i followed the spotlight in its direction, i could not see anything. but why this is so odd is that the spotlight was pointed straight out from the helicopter even with it occasionally lowering the angle and raised in the angle but it definitely was not as if it was a police or news chopper shining a light straight down to the ground looking for something, this hellicopter spotlight actually remained searching up in the sky itself hovering much of the time wit light pointed at something definately observing or searching, seeming like at times it was definitely in contact with some kind of target at times, though i never did see anything other than the three reds  lights i saw about 30 minutes earlier at apparently high altitude.
 one other thing about the helicopter,   though it was dark and i could not make out any defined surfaces, lights on both its port and starboard side extended out much farther than a normal helicopter almost as if it had small wings on it as an apache attack helicopter does for instance , and the noise it made was unlike anything commercial it was much more quiet though it was some distance away.

 i would say those are the main key points of the sighting. this is a legitimate true claim and ufo by definition. i do take great interest in astrophysics and ma stargazer whenever the sky permits it.  and have no gain in reporting such a thing i have read about sighting the three red lights and triangular aircraft i believe there's supposedly a military craft that's classified. is reported to be able to maneuver with these characteristics that i witnessed so that definitely gives more credibility to that theory but of course it could be something not from this world but it definitely is strange and a possible response to it by this helicopter made it even more strange from people who happened to see something in the night sky. this definitely was a very unusual and rare glimpse at something as a civilian.  the tries to see things that aren't there i literally saw this thing and at the very least if not aliens and all that jazz it was some kind of very high tech advanced aircraft developed by what i would guess might be the united states since it was passing over our air space when i saw it. very interesting sight i won't soon forget. thank you very much for taking the time. 

- corey
content.summary: 3 red light in triangular shape moved in straight line from w/sw towards e/ne at high altitude completely silent.

content.detailedDescription:
On 12/12/15, at 1:47 pm, i was driving my truck in henderson, nevada, on anthem pkwy, heading in a southwestern direction when i noticed a small disk shaped cloud.  the cloud peaked my interest since the las vegas sky was clear blue.  the only clouds present were way to the north over the sheep mountains.  i noticed that contrails were active on the exhaust of commercial jets flying overhead because of the cold, clear dessert air. so the little cloud peaked my interest, as it was all by itself, and so i thought, what could cause this small little cloud?  i slowed my vehicle, and took two pictures of the little cloud from my drivers seat using my new samsung galaxy s6 smartphone, which has a 16m pixel camera with image stabilization. i could not make anything out other then the disk shaped cloud since the sun was shining in my direction.  the pictures were dated by the camera as 20151212_134727 and 20151212_134752, which placed the time at exactly 1:47 pm.  i stayed in the street and watched the little cloud dissipate like an ordinary cloud.  it appeared to dissipate in about 20 seconds or so. the wind appeared to drift it towards the south. after the cloud dissipated, i thought nothing of it.  

after doing some chores, i was heading to get lunch.  it was now about 2:10 pm. i drove west bound on e. serene ave. (between pecos and eastern) and then noticed the small cloud again forward and off to my left.  the little cloud looked approximately in the same place as before and about the same size and shape.  now my interest was really peaked.  i pulled over to the side of the road, and clicked off five more pictures using my smartphone.  i could not see any detail, since the sun was again shining in my direction. i did not review the images, and i proceeded home.  

once at home, i looked at the pictures in more detail.  what i saw was really surprising.  two of the pictures show a whitish sphere adjacent to the cloud.  the last photo i snapped shows an arcing contrail like image that appears to start with the approximate location of the sphere, and ending in the cloud.  using approximate angles from my memory and two locations, (and assuming the object was indeed in the same place), i can triangulate the cloud to be approximately located over sloan.  this places the cloud about 7+ miles away from my first location.  

at the serene location, five pictures were taken over a 31 second period.  the first two photos, show only the small cloud and nothing else.  the next photo is 6 seconds later, and shows a spherical object colored just the same as the cloud.  the next picture two seconds later shows the object a little closer to the cloud.  the last picture, 19 seconds later, shows a contrail like arc entering the cloud.  so, in summary, first there is no object, 6 seconds later there is an object, and then 19 seconds later a contrail like arc going into the cloud.  

as the photos show, the cloud was changing shape a little during this 31 seconds, but this change is slow, which makes it hard to account for these spherical artifacts on the photos.  if the arc photo was taken before the two orb photos, i would have assumed that the orb was just a spot of cloud.  but in fact, as the time stamps show, its just the reverse, the orb appears first, then the arcing contrail appears last.  it's hard to imagine a little ball of cloud shearing into a distinct contrail like pattern and arcing in such a distinct way.  also, clearly evident in the two photos is that the spherical ball moves closer to the cloud in two seconds.

i haven't learned all the modes on my camera phone, as i now know i could have done a better job getting many more pictures, or even a video, but maybe next time!
content.summary: Sighted strange cloud, then cloud disappeared normally, then cloud came back hour later, with orbs.

content.detailedDescription: Just before 8:00 pm local time, my girlfriend, jessie, was walking eastward toward the back porch of my house after going out to check on our travel trailer which was parked about 200 feet west of the house. (see attached google earth screenshot for layout of the grounds.) she noticed two bright orange orbs glowing in the sky above the forest north of the hay pasture directly behind the house. she came in the house and to my office door where she asked me to come look at something. i got up from my desk and walked out the back bedroom door seconds later. she was looking up in the sky to the north and saying that they were gone. i asked what she had seen and after hearing her description of the glowing orbs, i indicated that seeing ufos in that direction was not that unusual. before i had finished speaking, i saw something orange moving through the treetops to the northeast and drew my girlfriend's attention to it. she became very excited as she spotted it saying that it was exactly what she had seen minutes earlier. we walked together northward toward the fence which separates the backyard from the hay pasture. as we walked, five orange glowing orbs came into view moving westward. they did not move in formation, but did move the same direction. relative speeds, distances of separation, and altitude varied noticeably between the objects as they tracked from right to left across our field of vision. there was no sound except that of the breeze which was blowing from the south steadily throughout the sighting. after about a minute had passed the objects had traversed approximately 30 to 40 degrees of our field of vision then one by one they just went out without a flash or sound. it appeared that each object gained altitude as it vanished from sight. the entire experience took less than 10 minutes.
content.summary: Orange glowing orbs at altitude moving generally e to w with altitude changes. two briefly due n, later five move in from e before vanishing.

cars were behind us and beeping. we see the ufo hovering so slowly up and to the side in the air. we slowly start moving the car and take a right to follow it but it was gone. we drove around but it was far from where we were.

content.detailedDescription:
I was in front of my house, returning home with my friend after a walk. i was about ten-years-old. my family lived in the woods in western south dakota. i saw an aircraft-like object that was diamond in shape. at first i thought it was a plane because we lived near an air force base, but it wasn't like any plane i had ever seen before: it was flying sideways in a vertical diamond shape, which drew our attention. the craft seemed to hover. we watched it for a while. it came closer to us and lowered in elevation. then, it disappeared over the horizon. we chatted for a while about it, and several minutes later i saw two tall, dark shapes emerging from the woods in the direction from where the ufo disappeared. they were taller than humans, approximately 15 feet, skinny, dark-toned. i couldn't make out any features. i was scared so i ran into the house; my friend didn't see them but followed me into the house, scared by my abrupt, terrified departure. this occurred at approximately 10:00 pm. 

later, at 1:00 am, i was alone in my room. i was reading in bed and listening to the radio. i went to sleep, turned off my light, and almost as soon as i turned off my light and got back into bed a red glowing light emerged from behind the blinds of my room's window. i was curious to see what was causing it, so i, remaining in bed, reached for the blind and pushed a few blind slots apart. it looked very blustery outside: debris was flying around, the trees were shaking. however, i couldn't hear a sound, and normally i could hear wind very clearly in that bedroom. the entire sky appeared dullish red. all of the objects outside also appeared red, as if there were a red lens over everything. i looked through the blinds for a literal second, maybe two, and then closed them in fear. almost as soon as i stopped looking the red light disappeared. i remained awake for the rest of the night, until dawn.         

since this occurred, on several occasions i have woken up in strange locations inside my house and, one time, in the backyard. i did not know how i had gotten there.
content.summary: Bifurcated event, first saw craft at distance, craft landed out of view, saw strange creatures in woods, later awakened by red light, observed heavy winds, no sound

content.detailedDescription: i was visiting my daughter in edgewater fl. i awoke and went outside for a smoke. i love to stargaze and while doing so i noticed a star or perhaps a sattelite moving through the trees. my attention was drawn to the star and 45 minutes to an hour later it was overhead heading out toward the atlantic. the star started out as a regular sized star and progressively grew in size until it was smaller than an asperin but larger than a star.   a few days later i deviloped an infection in my navel and had to use antiobotic ointment in it for a week before it cleared up. i have never had anything like this happen to me before. i felt very curious and watched through the trees as the star steadily grew in size, it made no sound at all . i have seen many sattelites in my life because i grew up on the space coast, but this was certainly something new to me. i have seen many unusual things my life but not like this one. my family think that i dream up all this stuff but believe me i have not.
content.summary: Feburary 2015 i witnessed a star move from the south west to the northeant in approximately an hour.

content.detailedDescription:
In bed top floor watching tv noticed fast moving object  through big glass doors

leapt out of bed and followed it through sky west to east silent and very bright red lights 

disappeared in 6/7 seconds maybe 10 covered at least 15miles maybe more fastest moving object i have ever seen

had to find somewhere to post so searched web
content.summary: Incredibly fast moving red glowing ball shape not a meteor for sure way too fast and not burning !

content.detailedDescription: Classic orb same as described in 2013 san antonio report. moving faster than an airplane but, not super fast. caught my eye when early morning sun 0920 or so, reflected off of it. reflected as if turning, not constant. could not determine altitude or size due to distance. definitely appeared to be well below 35.000ft plane flight paths. would guess maybe in the 12-15 thousand ft range. was due west over ocean but near the shore at about a 10 o'clock position. seemed to bobble slightly up and down accompanied w/a very thin haze. observed for appox. 20 sec. or so. heading due north and lost sight of it, as it went into (?) a very thin haze, in an otherwise cloudless sky. it was clear enough that i could tell that it was a sphere not cylindrical like an airplane.
content.summary: Silver orb observed appox. 0920 looking due west from the monterey peninsula bearing north toward santa cruz,ca.And san francisco.

content.detailedDescription: On november 25, 2015 at approxximately 7:00 p.M. i went outside in the front yard to smoke a cigarette. as i lit my cigarette i looked toward the east and over the sierra nevada mountain range i noticed a glowing red-orange oval shaped object that was stationary. ih know what an airoplane's lights look like but these didn't flash like the typical plane. i ran inside and yelled at my sister come quick look at this ... bring your cell phone which she dd. we both saw it and it didn't look like anything we had ever seen she capured it on video on her cell phone. it hovered in the east for a few minutes not moving and then zipped towards the south east eventually out of view. we both new this wasn't an everyday occurance. evidently, others also saw it because my sister said that the news said it was a meteor. but what kind of meteor hovers and stands still in one stationary place and then quickly "zips" off in another direction rapidly?
content.summary: Oval shape glowing and was bright red-orange in color
